Directory structure
===================
   test_2d_gc_cartesian                -- executable
   gcsim2d_curvilinear_input.nml       -- input file #1 ("Colella" mesh)
   gcsim2d_curvilinear_input_cart.nml  -- input file #2 (Cartesian mesh)
   gcsim2d_curvilinear_input_polar.nml -- input file #3 (polar mesh)
   gcsim2d_curvilinear_input_DSG.nml   -- input file #4 (D-shaped Tokamak sec.)
   README                              -- info (this file)
   run/                                -- output directory
   gcsim2d_curvilinear.gnu             -- gnuplot script #1
   gcsim2d_curvilinear_cart.gnu        -- gnuplot script #2 
   gcsim2d_curvilinear_polar.gnu       -- gnuplot script #3 
   gcsim2d_curvilinear_ref.dat         -- reference results (??)
   gcsim2d_cartesian_ref.dat           -- reference results #2
   gcsim2d_polar_ref.dat               -- reference results #3

HOWTO
=====
0. Create output directory if missing, and move into it
     $ mkdir run
     $ cd run

1. Run simulation within directory
     $ ../test_2d_gc_curvilinear ../gcsim2d_curvilinear_input_cart

2. Run included gnuplot script
     $ gnuplot --persist ../gcsim2d_curvilinear_cart.gnu

3. Open *.xmf database with Visit (*)


(*) Make sure that the Xdmf plugin is installed!

